.\"	$NetBSD: haudfw.1,v 1.1 2026/06/11 19:51:16 rumble Exp $
.Dd December 26, 2025
.Dt HAUDFW 1 sgimips
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm haudfw
.Nd convert a Hollywood Audio DSP .lod file to a firmware image
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Ar hdsp.lod
.Ar hdsp.bin
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
converts a Motorola DSP 56000 .lod file into a firmware blob that
.Xr haud 4
can load directly into the DSP's 32K-word SRAM. For use with SGI
Indigo and Personal Iris 4D/3x (IP12, IP20) machines.
.Pp
There is no open source firmware. The input file must be pulled from
an existing installation of IRIX or from install media. See
.Xr haud 4
for more details.
.Pp
The following options are available:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Fl c
Also output a C array of the converted firmware image to stdout.
.It Fl v
Increase debugging verbosity of stderr. Can be specified multiple times
to further increase logging.
.El
.Pp
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr haud 4 ,
.Xr undist 1
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
utility first appeared in
.Nx 12 .
